<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="979" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d979">
                    <head>Government of the Canton of Soleure</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 1, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>By the authority of the government counsellor of Solothurn, I hereby sign the
                        enclosed address of sympathy and condolence to the President of the United
                        States of North America, in the name of the canton of Solothurn.
                        (Soleure.)</p>
                    <p>For the Swiss Union Chancery:</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>SOHIESS,</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chancellor of the Confederation</hi>. </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p rend="flushleft">{Bundes-kanzlei Schweizeirsche Eidgenossenschaft.}</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>